import pyautogui
import time
import uiautomation as auto

try:
    auto.uiautomation.SetGlobalSearchTimeout(10)
    # Press Windows key to open Start menu
    pyautogui.press('win')
    time.sleep(1)
    # Type "word" to search for Microsoft Word
    pyautogui.write('word', interval=0.1)
    time.sleep(1)
    # Press Enter to launch the first result (Microsoft Word)
    pyautogui.press('enter')
    time.sleep(3)
    # Verify Word opened by checking for a top-level window
    word_window = auto.GetForegroundControl()
    if word_window and "word" in word_window.Name.lower():
        print("EXECUTION_SUCCESS")
    else:
        print("FAILED: Word window not detected")
except Exception as e:
    print("FAILED: " + str(e))
